      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO COMMANDO (6) comes back 100m and can fire off a solid effort a Wagga. Has plenty of his sleeve and the blinkers on for the first time. Boudvillain stays aboard and is striking at 31% with the Seib yard. SHOREMAN (8) is also back 100m and brings two narrow defeats from Canberra. Tumbles 6kgs and that brings him right into it. SNEAKY PEE CEE (5) won a Gundagai Maiden easily over 1000m and will keep improving for the strong local stable. Races forward and is sure to give a big sight. FELIS CHAUS (4) resumes for the Litt yard and was beaten 1L in his most recent Warwick Farm trial. Has decent form in stronger races and from an inside gate can feature. BIVACCO (1) needs a good ride but was much better at Scone and is in the mix.",
